My original characters were a dwarven fighter and an Erudite Enchanter. In RP games these I have played since Eye of the Beholder days, and in my AD&amp;D games, and they''re in my novel.<br>
However I found I coudlnt really PLAY them like I wanted to in EQ! :/<br>
Silverblade the Enchanter was a dashing silly rogue who acted like Fletch mixed with Marcus Cole from Babylon 5. Ok so I was brought up on films like Sinbad, The Crimson Pirate etc <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
But EQ is more 1st Person shoot em up with strategy and just a hint of Roleplaying, so its not really possible to PLAY that characters (ie he'd drive enemies loco, and often twist things around so they'd be his allies)  Also someone always has the name Silverblade, grr! :&gt;<br>
<br>
Hardaxe the dwarf was a fighter/thief. A battle loving, sneaky SOB with a  diehard heart and sense of humour.<br>
But you can't really be a fighter/thief in EQ, can't really be sneaky...<br>
<br>
So, Redorious was an NPC in games I DM'ed. A conjuror, wily, brilliant and though a foe of the heroes he wans't actually evil, he wanted a spellbook they had and knew that a demon prince was after it, and thought he should prevent the wrong folks getting it. Well as a conjuror he caused absolute HAVOC for my pal's characters, took them 2 real life years of adventures finally to put an end to him! They really enjoyed those stories, and later found a RESURRECTED and some what molified Redorious to be an ally when they ended up embroiled in a complex plot when one nations of Vikings were being used to invade the Empire they were in while it was being assaulted by legions of undead and drow. Redorious was an expert in elemental and humanoid creaures, having spent much of his life with orcs and thier ilk, serving as an advisor he tried civilizing them, and ended up as the Empire's ambassador to the tribes. He also ran a school where he found talented orphans of the brawling city and war shattered fmailes and taught them the ways of conjuration, so they wouldn't be weak and mere  pawns in the scheme of things.<br>
<br>
So in EQ, thought I'd try to be a conjuror, and found the ability to blow the absolute LIVING CRAP OUT OF EVERYTHING WAS FUN! MWAHAHHAAHHAH! :&gt;<br>
<br>
*coughs* Ahem...<br>
<br>
I also found the class very useful to folk in lots of odd different ways. You know the earring that drops in Chardok that usmons 20 water? Well while the item is woefully underpowered considering where its dropped..I've actually used it quite a lot <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
I enjoy the challenge of controling a dumb pet thats a walking disaster area (on either side depending on how it's used).<br>
The maniacal joy of burning down a heavy pull, of AOEing 20 mobs and acting like a pyromaniac Gandalf...<br>
CoH folks stuck and in dire need of help...<br>
Of pumping out mod rods so a raid buff session takes HALF the time...<br>
DS main tanks to do a SNOT load of damage to uber mobs...<br>
Researching spells, providing tips and Muzzles of Mardu for young mages...<br>
CRing newbies lost in the scary depths of Black Burrow (yeah admit it, BB scared the HELL out of you when you were a lowbie too!)<br>
Sitting in the entrance to Crushbone, seeing a horde of orcs chasing some screaming elves, pointing at them--<br>
Crying out &quot;Elemental, unleash the WRATH OF THE MAGI!&quot; and the bodies splatter off the walls as you incinerate the rest with the flaming wave of a Scintilation..<br>
While the brave tanks fight and die to Gorenaire's, frigid freezing blasts, you summons balls of elemntal fire that shatter ancient scales...<br>
The insidious, depraved horrors in the Plane of Hate who's unholy resistances are the bane of casters..YOU strip their protections assunder and let the forces of light scourge their blasphemous flesh...<br>
<br>
THESE ARE THE REASONS I PLAY A MAGE!<br>
<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Redorious<br>
Archmage<br>
karana<br>
